	<element name="Support Specialist" type="Class" source="JJK" id="ID_JJK_CLASS_SUPPORT_SPECIALIST">
		<description>
			<p>You support especially well.</p>
			<h3>CLASS FEATURES</h3>
			<p>As a support specialist, you gain the following class features.</p>
            <h5 class="caption">HIT POINTS</h5>
            <ul class="unstyled">
                <li><strong>Hit Dice:</strong> 1d6 per support specialist level</li>
                <li><strong>Hit Points at 1st Level:</strong> 6 + your Constitution modifier</li>
                <li><strong>Hit Points at Higher Levels:</strong> 1d6 (or 4) + your Constitution modifier per support specialist level after 1st</li>
            </ul>
            <h5 class="caption">PROFICIENCIES</h5>
            <ul class="unstyled mb">
                <li><strong>Armor:</strong> None</li>
                <li><strong>Weapons:</strong> Daggers, darts, slings, quarterstaffs, and handguns</li>
                <li><strong>Tools:</strong> None</li>
            </ul>
            <ul class="unstyled">
                <li><strong>Saving Throws:</strong> Intelligence, Wisdom</li>
                <li><strong>Skills:</strong> Choose two from Arcana, History, Insight, Investigation, Medicine, and Religion</li>
            </ul>
			<h5 class="caption">EQUIPMENT</h5>
			<p>You start with the following equipment, in addition to the equipment granted by your background:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>(a) a handgun or (b) a dagger</li>
				<li>(a) a component pouch or (b) an arcane focus</li>
				<li>(a) a scholar's pack or (b) an explorer's pack</li>
				<li>A technique manual</li>
			</ul>
			<h5 class="caption">THE SUPPORT SPECIALIST</h5>
			<table class="class-features">
				<thead>
					<tr><td class="col-10">Level</td><td class="col-10">Cursed Energy Points</td><td class="col-60 left">Features</td></tr>
				</thead>
				<tr><td>1st</td><td>1 + CE modifier + Prof</td><td class="left">Cursed Energy, Innate Technique, Curtain</td></tr>
				<tr><td>2nd</td><td>2 + CE modifier + Prof</td><td class="left">Barrier Techniques</td></tr>
				<tr><td>3rd</td><td>3 + CE modifier + Prof</td><td class="left">Innate Technique Feature</td></tr>
				<tr><td>4th</td><td>4 + CE modifier + Prof</td><td class="left">Ability Score Improvement</td></tr>
				<tr><td>5th</td><td>5 + CE modifier + Prof</td><td class="left">Reverse Curse Technique</td></tr>
				<tr><td>6th</td><td>6 + CE modifier + Prof</td><td class="left">Innate Technique Feature, Ability Score Improvement</td></tr>
				<tr><td>7th</td><td>7 + CE modifier + Prof</td><td class="left">Improved Curtain</td></tr>
				<tr><td>8th</td><td>8 + CE modifier + Prof</td><td class="left">Ability Score Improvement</td></tr>
				<tr><td>9th</td><td>9 + CE modifier + Prof</td><td class="left">Improved Barrier Technique</td></tr>
				<tr><td>10th</td><td>10 + CE modifier + Prof</td><td class="left">Reverse Curse Technique Understanding</td></tr>
				<tr><td>11th</td><td>11 + CE modifier + Prof</td><td class="left">Innate Technique Feature</td></tr>
				<tr><td>12th</td><td>12 + CE modifier + Prof</td><td class="left">Ability Score Improvement</td></tr>
				<tr><td>13th</td><td>13 + CE modifier + Prof</td><td class="left">Mastered Curtain</td></tr>
